  <refnamediv>
    <refname>inttrap</refname>

    <refpurpose>integration of experimental data by trapezoidal
    interpolation</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>v = inttrap([x,] s)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>x</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>vector of increasing x coordinate data. Default value is
          <literal>1:size(y,'*')</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>s</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>vector of y coordinate data</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>v</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>value of the integral</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>computes :</para>

    <para>Where f is a function described by a set of experimental
    value:</para>

    <para><literal>s(i)=f(x(i))</literal> and <literal>x0=x(1)</literal>,
    <literal>x1=x(n)</literal></para>

    <para>Between mesh points function is interpolated linearly.</para>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <programlisting role="example"> 
t=0:0.1:%pi
inttrap(t,sin(t))
   </programlisting>
  </refsection>

